Our mission is to protect and promote the rights, interests, and well-being of the indigenous peoples of Fiji, by preserving their ancestral lands, fishing areas, and resources, as well as their cultural heritage, traditional knowledge, and evolving traditions.

We strive to achieve this by raising awareness, advocating for policy changes, providing education and capacity-building opportunities, and fostering collaboration and dialogue among all stakeholders, including indigenous communities, government agencies, civil society organizations, and the private sector.
